TITLE: Registering Image Block Variation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example of registering a custom 'wide-image' variation for the core/image block using the get_block_type_variations filter in PHP.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/block-api/block-variations.md#2025-04-21_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
function my_custom_image_variation( $variations, $block_type ) {
    // Only modify variations for the image block
    if ( 'core/image' !== $block_type->name ) {
        return $variations;
    }

    // Add a custom variation
    $variations[] = array(
		'name'        => 'wide-image',
		'title'       => __( 'Wide image', 'textdomain' ),
		'description' => __( 'A wide image', 'textdomain' ),
		'scope'       => array( 'inserter' ),
		'isDefault'   => false,
		'attributes'  => array(
			'align' => 'wide', // Identifies the link type as custom
		),
    );

    return $variations;
}
add_filter( 'get_block_type_variations', 'my_custom_image_variation', 10, 2 );
```

