TITLE: Implementing Async Actions with Generators in JavaScript for WordPress Gutenberg
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement async actions using generators in the WordPress Gutenberg Interactivity API. It shows how to properly handle context and state in asynchronous operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/interactivity-api/api-reference.md#2025-04-21_snippet_30

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { state } = store( 'myPlugin', {
	state: {
		get isOpen() {
			return getContext().isOpen;
		},
	},
	actions: {
		someAction: function* () {
			state.isOpen; // This context is correct because it's synchronous.
			yield longDelay(); // With generators, the caller controls when to resume this function.
			state.isOpen; // This context is correct because we restored the proper scope before we resumed the function.
		},
	},
} );
```

