TITLE: Registering Plugin using ESNext
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to register a plugin with the Gutenberg editor using ESNext syntax. It utilizes `PluginSidebar` and `PluginSidebarMoreMenuItem` components from `@wordpress/editor` to create a sidebar plugin. The `registerPlugin` function from `@wordpress/plugins` registers the plugin with specified configurations, including an icon, a render function (which returns the React components for the sidebar), and a scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/packages/plugins/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
"// Using ESNext syntax
import { PluginSidebar, PluginSidebarMoreMenuItem } from '@wordpress/editor';
import { registerPlugin } from '@wordpress/plugins';
import { more } from '@wordpress/icons';

const Component = () => (
	<>
		<PluginSidebarMoreMenuItem target="sidebar-name">
			My Sidebar
		</PluginSidebarMoreMenuItem>
		<PluginSidebar name="sidebar-name" title="My Sidebar">
			Content of the sidebar
		</PluginSidebar>
	</>
);

registerPlugin( 'plugin-name', {
	icon: more,
	render: Component,
	scope: 'my-page',
} );"
```

