TITLE: Registering a Custom Block with InnerBlocks
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet shows how to register a custom block in the WordPress Gutenberg editor that uses InnerBlocks to manage nested block content. The edit function uses InnerBlocks to allow users to add blocks within the custom block, and the save function uses InnerBlocks.Content to store the nested blocks' content. Dependencies include the WordPress block-editor and blocks modules. The main purpose is to enable block nesting within custom blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/packages/block-editor/src/components/inner-blocks/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { registerBlockType } from '@wordpress/blocks';
import { useBlockProps, InnerBlocks } from '@wordpress/block-editor';

registerBlockType( 'my-plugin/my-block', {
	// ...

	edit() {
		const blockProps = useBlockProps();

		return (
			<div { ...blockProps }>
				<InnerBlocks />
			</div>
		);
	},

	save() {
		const blockProps = useBlockProps.save();

		return (
			<div { ...blockProps }>
				<InnerBlocks.Content />
			</div>
		);
	},
} );
```

