TITLE: Enqueuing CSS Styles for Custom Block Editor in WordPress
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code enqueues both WordPress default formatting library styles and custom CSS styles for the block editor. It uses wp_enqueue_style() to register the styles with appropriate handles and dependencies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/how-to-guides/platform/custom-block-editor.md#2025-04-21_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// Enqueue default editor styles.
wp_enqueue_style( 'wp-format-library' );

// Enqueue custom styles.
wp_enqueue_style(
    'getdave-sbe-styles',                       // Handle
    plugins_url( 'build/index.css', __FILE__ ), // Block editor CSS
    array( 'wp-edit-blocks' ),                  // Dependency to include the CSS after it
    filemtime( __DIR__ . '/build/index.css' )
);
```

