TITLE: Creating Custom Middleware for API Fetch
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create and use a custom middleware with API Fetch. This example creates a middleware that logs the time taken for each request to complete.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/packages/api-fetch/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import apiFetch from '@wordpress/api-fetch';

apiFetch.use( ( options, next ) => {
	const start = Date.now();
	const result = next( options );
	result.then( () => {
		console.log( 'The request took ' + ( Date.now() - start ) + 'ms' );
	} );
	return result;
} );
```

