TITLE: Creating a Registry Selector - WordPress - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: The createRegistrySelector function initializes a selector function allowing selection from other registered stores using a curried select argument. It facilitates querying across multiple stores without manually passing a registry.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/packages/data/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { store as coreStore } from '@wordpress/core-data';
import { store as editorStore } from '@wordpress/editor';

const getCurrentPostId = createRegistrySelector( ( select ) => ( state ) => {
	return select( editorStore ).getCurrentPostId();
} );

const getPostEdits = createRegistrySelector( ( select ) => ( state ) => {
	const postType = getCurrentPostType( state );
	const postId = getCurrentPostId( state );
	return select( coreStore ).getEntityRecordEdits(
		'postType',
		postType,
		postId
	);
} );
```

