TITLE: Setting Cross-Origin Attribute for Media in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to set the crossOrigin attribute for foreign-origin media elements using a JavaScript filter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/filters/editor-filters.md#2025-04-21_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { addFilter } from '@wordpress/hooks';

addFilter(
	'media.crossOrigin',
	'my-plugin/with-cors-media',
	// The callback accepts a second `mediaSrc` argument which references
	// the url to actual foreign media, useful if you want to decide
	// the value of crossOrigin based upon it.
	( crossOrigin, mediaSrc ) => {
		if ( mediaSrc.startsWith( 'https://example.com' ) ) {
			return 'use-credentials';
		}
		return crossOrigin;
	}
);
```

