TITLE: Updating Array Attributes Immutably
DESCRIPTION: Shows the correct way to update array attributes immutably using the spread operator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/block-api/block-edit-save.md#2025-04-21_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Good - a new array is created from the old list attribute and a new list item:
const { list } = attributes;
const addListItem = ( newListItem ) =>
	setAttributes( { list: [ ...list, newListItem ] } );

// Bad - the list from the existing attribute is modified directly to add the new list item:
const { list } = attributes;
const addListItem = ( newListItem ) => {
	list.push( newListItem );
	setAttributes( { list } );
};
```

