TITLE: Filtering allowed block types
DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet filters the list of blocks shown in the inserter using the `allowed_block_types_all` filter. It allows only `core/paragraph` and `core/heading` blocks when a post is being edited, otherwise it returns the original allowed block types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/filters/block-filters.md#2025-04-21_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php
// my-plugin.php
function example_filter_allowed_block_types_when_post_provided( $allowed_block_types, $editor_context ) {
	if ( ! empty( $editor_context->post ) ) {
		return array( 'core/paragraph', 'core/heading' );
	}
	return $allowed_block_types;
}
add_filter( 'allowed_block_types_all', 'example_filter_allowed_block_types_when_post_provided', 10, 2 );

```

