TITLE: Typing Asynchronous Actions with Generators
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to type asynchronous actions using generator functions and handle their return types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/reference-guides/interactivity-api/core-concepts/using-typescript.md#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { state } = store( 'myCounterPlugin', {
	state: {
		counter: 0,
		get double(): number {
			return state.counter * 2;
		},
	},
	actions: {
		increment() {
			state.counter += 1;
		},
		*delayedIncrement() {
			yield new Promise( ( r ) => setTimeout( r, 1000 ) );
			state.counter += 1;
		},
	},
} );
