TITLE: Using Hierarchical Term Selector for Non-Hierarchical Taxonomy in WordPress Gutenberg using JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the HierarchicalTermSelector component for a non-hierarchical taxonomy. By adding a filter to 'editor.PostTaxonomyType', this code allows the 'track' taxonomy to render as a hierarchical selector while still using the original component for other taxonomies.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/packages/editor/src/components/post-taxonomies/README.md#2025-04-21_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const el = React.createElement;
const HierarchicalTermSelector = wp.editor.PostTaxonomiesHierarchicalTermSelector;

function customizeTrackSelector( OriginalComponent ) {
	return function ( props ) {
		if ( props.slug === 'track' ) {
			return el( HierarchicalTermSelector, props );
		} else {
			return el( OriginalComponent, props );
		}
	};
}

wp.hooks.addFilter(
	'editor.PostTaxonomyType',
	'my-plugin/set-hierarchical-term-selector',
	customizeTrackSelector
);
```

