TITLE: Applying Block Styles in Gutenberg
DESCRIPTION: This JSON snippet demonstrates how to apply styles to specific blocks and the document body using `theme.json`. It sets the body text color, overrides the text color for the `core/paragraph` block using the `p` selector, and applies a text color to the `core/group` block using the `.wp-block-group` selector. This showcases the cascading nature of styles and how to target specific blocks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/wordpress/gutenberg/blob/trunk/docs/how-to-guides/themes/global-settings-and-styles.md#2025-04-21_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
	"version": 3,
	"styles": {
		"color": {
			"text": "var(--wp--preset--color--primary)"
		},
		"blocks": {
			"core/paragraph": {
				"color": {
					"text": "var(--wp--preset--color--secondary)"
				}
			},
			"core/group": {
				"color": {
					"text": "var(--wp--preset--color--tertiary)"
				}
			}
		}
	}
}
```

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
body {
	color: var( --wp--preset--color--primary );
}
p { /* The core/paragraph opts out from the default behaviour and uses p as a selector. */
	color: var( --wp--preset--color--secondary );
}
.wp-block-group {
	color: var( --wp--preset--color--tertiary );
}
```

